  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Surgical amputation of the left atrial appendage (LAA) is an established intervention during
      surgical atrial fibrillation (AF) therapy. However, its effects on the endocrine function of
      the left atrium are unclear. This study aims to quantify the serum levels of natriuretic
      peptides in patients who undergo concomitant surgical AF ablation with or without LAA
      amputation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
